  "stem": "<p>If <math><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>, what is the value of <math><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mi>y</mi></mfrac></math>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": null,
  "keys": [".25", "1/4"],
  "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is <math><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>. Since <math><mn>4</mn></math> can be written as <math><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></math>, the equation <math><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math> is equivalent to <math><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></math>, so <math><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mi>y</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>. Alternatively, multiplying both sides by 6 gives <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn></math>, and <math><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>24</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>. Both .25 and 1/4 are accepted.</p>",
